[upbeat music]

01:07.875 --> 01:14.875
♪ ♪

01:24.417 --> 01:25.417
- Hi.

01:25.417 --> 01:27.000
- Hi.
- How are you?

01:27.042 --> 01:28.875
Are you sleeping?

01:28.917 --> 01:32.792
I'm sorry babe, so anyways,
I'm tired and stressed out

01:32.792 --> 01:34.458
because it's the end
of the season,

01:34.458 --> 01:38.792
and I feel like a lot
of the crew has just given up.

01:38.792 --> 01:40.458
Emily and Sierra seem to think

01:40.458 --> 01:42.708
the charter season's over,
and it's not.

01:42.750 --> 01:44.083
If they want the last tip,

01:44.125 --> 01:45.875
they need to do
the last few days of work.

01:45.917 --> 01:49.917
Do the details really matter?

01:49.958 --> 01:52.958
You can tell I'm upset, right?
Maybe you should, like,

01:52.958 --> 01:56.792
understand that something's up
and be supportive?

01:56.792 --> 01:59.792
[light techno music]

01:59.792 --> 02:06.833
♪ ♪

02:10.125 --> 02:13.667
- Today's Thursday, right?
- Yeah.

02:13.667 --> 02:15.250
- It's disappointing that
Captain Lee

02:15.292 --> 02:16.917
doesn't have 100% faith in me

02:16.958 --> 02:18.667
that I'm gonna
get the job done.

02:18.667 --> 02:20.417
But I just want to prove
that he was right

02:20.458 --> 02:22.000
in choosing me as the bosun.

02:22.000 --> 02:24.000
Kyle, you were on early
last time, right?

02:24.000 --> 02:27.833
- Yeah.

02:27.833 --> 02:29.792
- F---, this doesn't work.

02:30.833 --> 02:33.833
[upbeat music]

02:33.833 --> 02:38.500
♪ ♪

02:38.500 --> 02:40.833
There he is.
- There the devil is.

02:40.833 --> 02:43.667
Both Ems and I,
we had a great time.

02:43.667 --> 02:47.792
It was nice to become more
comfortable with one another.

02:47.833 --> 02:51.167
- Have a good nap.
[laughter]

02:51.167 --> 02:52.542
- That's all you get.

02:54.208 --> 02:57.208
[driving techno music]

02:57.208 --> 03:00.333
♪ ♪

03:00.375 --> 03:02.000
- How's Ashley?
- Seriously, it was

03:02.042 --> 03:03.667
so cool actually meeting her.

03:03.708 --> 03:05.542
Like, you guys are
two peas in a pod.

03:05.542 --> 03:10.292
- She took the Sierra situation
quite nicely.

03:10.333 --> 03:12.167
- I didn't want to say it
but did you tell her about that?

03:12.208 --> 03:13.833
- I'm not gonna f---ing
not tell her, am I?

03:13.875 --> 03:15.542
- No, no, I just was curious
about what happened.

03:15.542 --> 03:17.375
- I'm a big person
about telling the truth...

03:17.375 --> 03:19.167
- No, I understand you are.
- 'Cause I never used to.

03:19.208 --> 03:20.625
I've been around the world
and there's one thing

03:20.667 --> 03:22.375
that I've learned
is beautiful women,

03:22.375 --> 03:23.792
and when I'm around them
I just can't help myself.

03:23.833 --> 03:26.000
I come for them
all guns blazing.

03:26.042 --> 03:28.000
Should I have done it knowing
that there was

03:28.042 --> 03:30.708
an on and off relationship
with Ashley back home?

03:30.708 --> 03:32.750
Maybe not.
The thing is...

03:39.083 --> 03:42.417
It's like, "I know."
I knew she wouldn't like her.

03:42.417 --> 03:45.458
- That's because Sierra's
a different breed.

03:52.583 --> 03:53.917
- Ben, Kate, Kelley,

03:53.917 --> 03:55.917
I need you guys down
in the crew mess

03:55.917 --> 03:58.583
