27:04.625 --> 27:08.625
- Whoo!
- Hey, Ben, a lot of the guests

27:08.625 --> 27:10.125
are out of their cabins

27:10.125 --> 27:12.375
and I think
they're shooting for 8:30.

27:12.417 --> 27:15.250
- Very well, thank you.
- Bye.

27:15.292 --> 27:16.458
- Sayonara, Jason.
- Thank you.

27:16.500 --> 27:20.458
- Thank you so much. Bye.

27:23.167 --> 27:25.750
- What's that, the ending dance?

27:25.792 --> 27:30.167
- Do we have assigned seating?
- This is good; this is good.

27:30.167 --> 27:32.667
- The guests are at the table.

27:32.667 --> 27:35.000
- Listen, Kelley,
I love you, bro,

27:35.000 --> 27:38.333
but I just, you know?
I...

27:38.333 --> 27:42.958
- Look, I...
[inaudible]

27:43.000 --> 27:44.667
- I'm just--

27:44.667 --> 27:46.125
- I know you're very much
a person who if you don't

27:46.167 --> 27:47.500
like somebody
you don't give a sh--,

27:47.500 --> 27:50.333
but in confined places,
we need you to give

27:50.333 --> 27:51.667
a little bit of a sh--.

27:51.667 --> 27:53.792
Just a little bit.
I need you to.

27:53.833 --> 27:56.542
- I just want to get off
this boat now--I'm over it.

27:56.542 --> 27:59.708
Sierra,
she's the f---ing devil.

27:59.708 --> 28:01.125
- I did not mean
to be rude to you.

28:01.167 --> 28:02.708
I was trying to say...
- I didn't do--

28:02.708 --> 28:04.542
- How you come across--how you
came across to all of us.

28:04.542 --> 28:06.292
- By picking up his radio?

28:06.333 --> 28:08.208
I did nothing, Kelley, but--no.

28:08.208 --> 28:09.708
- No, no, no, no, how you were
talking to all of us.

28:09.708 --> 28:11.208
We wouldn't mess
with your radio.

28:11.208 --> 28:12.833
The only reason we were
doing it with Lauren is

28:12.875 --> 28:15.375
because she's part of my crew.
So your coming--

28:15.375 --> 28:17.542
- I thought you were teasing me,
and by me picking up his radio--

28:17.542 --> 28:18.875
- We would never tease you.

28:18.875 --> 28:20.708
When have we teased you?
When have we--

28:20.708 --> 28:22.458
- Can you stop talking over me?
I feel like it's more often

28:22.500 --> 28:23.958
than not an unpleasant encounter
every time I deal with you.

28:24.000 --> 28:25.708
This is yet another time

28:25.708 --> 28:27.875
that he's inserted his nose
where he doesn't belong.

28:27.875 --> 28:29.042
- I just don't want you
blaming Kyle.

28:29.042 --> 28:31.125
You did not tell him the truth.

28:31.167 --> 28:33.000
- You shouldn't be judging me.
I'm over him; I'm over Kyle.

28:33.042 --> 28:35.208
When I leave this boat,
I'm not talking to you anymore.

28:35.208 --> 28:37.000
- How you talk to people,
like this right here,

28:37.042 --> 28:38.042
is just disrespectful...
- Yeah.

28:38.083 --> 28:39.500
- And how you came across

28:39.542 --> 28:41.167
to everybody out there
was disrespectful.

28:41.208 --> 28:42.583
- When Kyle starts yelling
at me for doing nothing...

28:42.583 --> 28:44.542
- Yes it was.
- But picking up his radio?

28:44.583 --> 28:46.000
- You were rude before that.
- I'm over it. No, I wasn't.

28:46.042 --> 28:47.333
- You were rude before that.
Yes, you were.

28:47.375 --> 28:49.208
- No, I wasn't.
- Other people noted it.

28:49.250 --> 28:50.917
- I don't have this problem
with anybody but you and Kyle.

28:50.917 --> 28:52.750
I don't need to talk
to you anymore.

28:52.750 --> 28:55.000
Let's just not speak, cool?
- Okay, well, guess what?

28:55.042 --> 28:57.208
We work in a place together,
and we do have to work together.

28:57.250 --> 28:58.708
- Okay, for the next
two days, okay.

28:58.750 --> 29:02.583
- Grow up.
- Cool.

29:02.583 --> 29:03.875
- Don't.

29:14.250 --> 29:16.375
And the funny thing is,
is when she does laundry,

29:16.417 --> 29:17.917
nobody gets their shirts right.

29:17.917 --> 29:19.292
She can't do her
f---ing job right.

29:19.292 --> 29:22.125
She walks around...
- [laughing]

29:22.125 --> 29:24.125
Oh, God.

29:24.125 --> 29:26.917
- I couldn't last.
I love to eat.

29:26.958 --> 29:28.417
I'm like you, I'm half Italian,
half Irish...

29:28.458 --> 29:30.750
- Oh, yeah.
- I love to eat.

29:30.792 --> 29:33.583
- I just lost it on Kelley, too.
- What's going on?

29:33.625 --> 29:35.125
Tell me what happened.

29:35.125 --> 29:36.208
- Nothing, like--
- What do you mean nothing?

29:36.250 --> 29:37.417
- I was like "where's my radio?"

29:37.458 --> 29:39.083
And I picked up Kyle's...

29:39.125 --> 29:40.625
- To check, yeah.
- Just to see, but I didn't--

29:40.625 --> 29:42.458
I couldn't see whose it was
so he, like,

29:42.458 --> 29:44.208
took it like I was accusing him
of stealing it,

29:44.250 --> 29:45.625
and he freaked out so bad.

29:45.625 --> 29:46.708
He's like,
"You're a f---ing idiot,

29:46.750 --> 29:48.875
Why would I have your radio?"

29:48.917 --> 29:50.750
Kelley's like, "You're giving
him an attitude," and I'm like,

29:50.792 --> 29:52.750
"No I'm not, like--"
- Oh, man.

29:52.792 --> 29:56.125
I don't have time to deal
with another Sierra freak-out,

29:56.167 --> 29:59.792
because all I have time
for is the job we're doing.

29:59.792 --> 30:01.917
- Why are they so mean to me?

30:01.958 --> 30:03.833
It's just those two.

30:03.833 --> 30:05.917
I know in a day he'll come back
to me, like, "I'm really sorry."

30:05.958 --> 30:07.792
But I'll already be over it.

30:07.833 --> 30:10.458
- No, actually, I'm not gonna
say sorry to you this time.

30:10.500 --> 30:11.500
- Good.

30:11.500 --> 30:13.167
- Really?
- Yeah, really.

30:13.167 --> 30:14.833
I was actually having Kyle

30:14.833 --> 30:18.000
come to you to apologize,
but you blew up at me.

30:18.000 --> 30:21.125
So sometimes being able to
communicate and talk to people,

30:21.167 --> 30:22.667
and you take everything
as an assault

30:22.667 --> 30:24.500
when it wasn't--whatever.

30:24.500 --> 30:27.917
- I take everything with salt.
- A grain of it. Only one.

30:27.958 --> 30:29.667
- No, I mean, when I cook.

30:31.458 --> 30:34.167
[laughing]

30:34.167 --> 30:35.750
- I'm gonna keep the peace,

30:35.792 --> 30:37.667
finish my work
and leave this boat.

30:37.667 --> 30:40.667
[dramatic music]

30:40.667 --> 30:44.667
♪ ♪

30:44.708 --> 30:46.833
- You're gonna look so good
washing dishes in that.

30:46.875 --> 30:50.500
- I know.

30:50.542 --> 30:52.625
- All right,
I think we're ready.

30:52.667 --> 30:55.125
- Yay.

30:55.167 --> 30:57.833
- What do we have tonight?
- Here we have a truffle

30:57.875 --> 31:00.167
panko-crusted Chilean sea bass.

31:00.208 --> 31:01.875
- Wow.
- Yum!

31:01.875 --> 31:03.542
- Thank you so much.
- Delish.

31:03.542 --> 31:04.875
- I'd love to meet the chef
at some point

31:04.875 --> 31:06.292
if I could
because he is phenomenal.

31:06.333 --> 31:09.167
- Oh, he will come out.
- Do you hear that?

31:09.208 --> 31:11.625
You're giving them an orgasm,
right now.

31:11.667 --> 31:15.292
[upbeat music]

31:15.333 --> 31:16.833
- Amazing.
- Every single thing--

31:16.875 --> 31:18.833
need to meet the chef.

31:18.875 --> 31:22.458
- They're so happy that you have
to bring the dessert out,

31:22.500 --> 31:26.875
because they want to meet you.

31:26.917 --> 31:30.042
- Oh, I love a Foster.
- Me, too.

31:30.083 --> 31:31.833
- I'm gonna come out with you.
- Come on.

31:31.875 --> 31:34.000
- Look at this.
- Here's our beautiful chef.

31:34.042 --> 31:37.583
- It's him! Wait, whoo!

31:37.583 --> 31:40.583
- Standing ovations for Ben!
- No, no, no.

31:40.583 --> 31:42.250
- Delicious!
- Top notch.

31:42.250 --> 31:46.500
- Can we get a hug and
a kiss, or no?

31:46.542 --> 31:49.875
- Mm-hmm.

31:49.917 --> 31:51.417
- All right.

31:51.417 --> 31:56.583
- Good to see you, good night.
- Oh, I love you.

31:56.583 --> 31:59.042
- I used to be a werewolf,
but I'm over it now.

31:59.083 --> 32:06.458
♪ ♪

32:06.458 --> 32:09.583
- All right, goodnight, baby.
- Night, night.

32:11.917 --> 32:13.292
- Would you do it again?
- Yeah.

32:13.292 --> 32:14.792
The f---ing money's amazing.

32:14.792 --> 32:16.542
- Yeah, and it's fun.
- Yeah.

32:16.583 --> 32:19.125
- And you meet
really amazing people.

32:21.792 --> 32:24.417
- I don't get that.
I just--I don't get it.

32:29.250 --> 32:32.125
- No, she's f---ing...
[whistles]

32:35.750 --> 32:38.250
- You know, everyone has
their own sh--, like,

32:38.292 --> 32:40.042
you know, Kate--
she's a sh-- stirrer,

32:40.083 --> 32:42.417
and just the way
she talks to the girls, like--

32:42.458 --> 32:46.458
- She's a f---ing bitch.
- Yeah.

32:46.458 --> 32:48.667
- Are you going down now?
- I can't sleep, babe,

32:48.667 --> 32:51.292
you know that.
I have real problems.

32:51.333 --> 32:53.667
- Real problems.
- I don't know,

32:53.667 --> 32:55.292
I just--I'm worked up.

32:55.333 --> 32:57.083
I just got worked up.
I'm fine now, though.

32:57.125 --> 32:58.958
I don't really have
much anxiety anymore.

32:59.000 --> 33:01.583
- When did that happen, today?
- Well you're--you helped me,

33:01.625 --> 33:04.333
because you've been
nicer to me, you know?

33:04.333 --> 33:07.167
- Today?
- A little bit I feel, yeah.

33:07.167 --> 33:08.292
- Yeah, you know what
my technique was?

33:08.333 --> 33:09.500
- What?

33:09.500 --> 33:10.833
- I avoided you as much as
possible

33:10.833 --> 33:14.833
so that I wasn't as annoyed.

33:14.833 --> 33:17.625
- You know, like,
I properly f---ing

33:17.667 --> 33:19.292
hate you sometimes.

33:19.333 --> 33:21.458
Like, I want to kill you.
- I really--I really--

33:21.500 --> 33:23.417
- I've worked with Kate
for years,

33:23.458 --> 33:25.292
and I've never
really understood

33:25.333 --> 33:27.667
why her moods
are so up and down.

33:27.667 --> 33:29.375
But I can tell you one thing:

33:29.375 --> 33:32.458
Kate is such an easy person
to work with,

33:32.500 --> 33:33.958
like Attila the Hun.

33:34.000 --> 33:35.333
- Sometimes you don't
even have to talk.

33:35.375 --> 33:37.458
I just look at you,
and I hate you.

33:37.500 --> 33:41.208
- I know.
- Like, a lot.

33:41.208 --> 33:43.000
- And I go check
all the cabins.

33:43.042 --> 33:45.458
The trashes are full; three of
the rooms have no toilet paper.

33:45.500 --> 33:47.333
The job's not done, clearly you
haven't been working enough.

33:47.375 --> 33:49.000
We don't need breaks.

33:57.625 --> 33:58.417
- What's the game plan?

33:58.042 --> 33:58.417
- When we get there,

34:00.542 --> 34:02.000
you guys will have about
a 40-minute cab ride

34:02.042 --> 34:03.292
and then a little,
quick walk down,

34:03.333 --> 34:04.833
experience the baths and--

34:04.875 --> 34:06.333
- Yeah, we want to spend
as much time

34:06.375 --> 34:09.000
as we can just really
exploring that, yeah.

34:09.042 --> 34:12.000
- Outside.
- Yeah, whatever you guys like.

34:12.042 --> 34:15.000
[playful music]

34:15.042 --> 34:21.042
♪ ♪

34:21.083 --> 34:22.917
- Hey, Ben,
do you have a banana?

34:22.917 --> 34:24.833
- Yeah, I've got one.
- F---ing need something.

34:24.875 --> 34:31.208
♪ ♪

34:31.250 --> 34:32.375
- Cabins.

34:32.417 --> 34:34.083
- Downstairs?
- Cabins.

34:34.083 --> 34:36.583
- They're all up.
- This is not a new system.

34:36.583 --> 34:37.917
When the guests
are having breakfast,

34:37.958 --> 34:40.667
we go tidy their cabins
and make the beds.

34:40.708 --> 34:43.375
When the guests are having
dinner, we go tidy their cabins

34:43.417 --> 34:46.667
and turn down their beds.

34:46.708 --> 34:48.208
- Hey--
- You're going to the baths

34:48.250 --> 34:49.917
with Kyle,

34:49.917 --> 34:53.208
so get everything you need
prepped and put into the Rib.

34:53.250 --> 34:54.625
- All right, sounds good.

34:54.625 --> 34:56.708
- We're just getting
into stride.

34:56.750 --> 34:57.958
- I know.
- People are starting

34:57.958 --> 34:58.917
to crack, though.

34:58.958 --> 35:00.542
- Who?
- The stews.

35:00.583 --> 35:03.458
Sierra's about to lose it.

35:03.458 --> 35:05.042
- Let's pull
the snapper, please.

35:05.083 --> 35:07.292
- Everyone put Necker Island
for me.

35:07.292 --> 35:09.917
I'm like, "Richard Branson's
my inspiration."

35:09.958 --> 35:12.750
- Fire them up at will.
- Copy that, firing up.

35:14.958 --> 35:17.042
- I didn't realize when I was
in the bathroom, like, oh wait,

35:17.083 --> 35:18.708
we have two more
closets over here

35:18.750 --> 35:20.292
at the side of the bathroom.

35:20.292 --> 35:21.917
We always did everything
manually in the little boat,

35:21.958 --> 35:23.708
so it was like throwing out
the anchor--

35:23.750 --> 35:25.708
- What's that little island
straight ahead to the right?

35:25.750 --> 35:28.042
- Yeah, you're
turning the wrong way.

35:28.083 --> 35:29.792
- I'm waving the white flag;
I give up.

35:29.792 --> 35:31.417
- Is there anywhere
you can sit and drive

35:31.458 --> 35:34.125
or do you always have to stand?

35:34.167 --> 35:36.125
- You want to go see it?
- Okay.

35:36.167 --> 35:38.083
- So if you see
the bottom of it?

35:38.125 --> 35:41.667
- Oh, yeah. So cool.
It's huge.

35:41.667 --> 35:45.792
- Sometimes I just love being
able to delegate, and this guest

35:45.833 --> 35:48.333
not being my problem anymore
is one of them.

35:48.333 --> 35:50.792
- Anchor's home and secure.
- Oh, look at that.

35:50.833 --> 35:53.667
Is that, like, the engine room?

35:53.667 --> 35:57.333
- Oh, that's beautiful.
- Amazing, thank you.

35:57.333 --> 35:59.167
- Can I get you
ladies anything else?

35:59.167 --> 36:01.000
- No, thank you, it's all set.

36:01.000 --> 36:04.167
- You're welcome.

36:04.167 --> 36:06.250
- F---ing always, always,

36:06.292 --> 36:09.417
always underway, breakfast.

36:09.458 --> 36:11.458
No coordination
with the interior.

36:11.500 --> 36:14.250
F--- off, everyone.

36:14.292 --> 36:18.375
12-foot swells during breakfast,
oh, pfft, not a big deal.

36:18.375 --> 36:22.500
Keep rolling on, you know?
It's all good; they'll be fine.

36:22.542 --> 36:24.625
- Hi.
- No, it's really appetizing,

36:24.667 --> 36:26.042
and it's not dangerous as all.

36:26.042 --> 36:31.042
- We only have 26 hours
and 51 minutes.

36:31.042 --> 36:32.500
- All right, broccoli
and [inaudible].

36:32.542 --> 36:34.542
- Shockingly, Ben is the person

36:34.542 --> 36:37.208
I'm least annoyed
with this charter.

36:37.208 --> 36:40.042
- Who's that for?
- It's for the captain.

36:40.042 --> 36:43.792
- All right, can we feed
the guests?

36:43.833 --> 36:46.125
- Nico?
- Yo.

36:46.167 --> 36:48.958
- Yeah, I'll just give it
to the girls--make them do it.

36:54.375 --> 36:58.583
- Do you know what I mean?
- Excuse me?

36:58.583 --> 37:02.167
- Sure, can you hose this out?
- Cheers. Uh-huh.

37:04.417 --> 37:06.250
There you go.
Here you are, cheers.

37:06.250 --> 37:07.583
- Oh, this is unbelievable.

37:07.583 --> 37:09.250
This is right up your alley.

37:09.250 --> 37:11.417
- Grapefruit juice?
- Yeah, it's really good.

37:11.417 --> 37:13.042
That's the grapefruit?
- Yeah.

37:13.083 --> 37:15.875
- Oh, my God.
- What's the matter?

37:15.917 --> 37:18.250
- I've just been, like,
running since literally 6:00

37:18.250 --> 37:19.750
and, like, I'm cool with that,

37:19.750 --> 37:21.250
but then, like,
the deck team's asking me

37:21.250 --> 37:23.042
to do all their jobs,
like fill the cooler.

37:23.083 --> 37:25.000
- No.
- You know, and I'm just like

37:25.042 --> 37:27.667
"Dude, there's one of me."
- Okay, fine.

37:27.708 --> 37:29.542
Deck crew, deck crew, Kate.

37:29.583 --> 37:30.917
- Go for deck crew.

37:30.917 --> 37:32.833
- Will you come to
the stew pantry, please?

37:32.875 --> 37:34.417
- Yeah, will do.

37:34.417 --> 37:35.750
- It's just, like,
one thing after another...

37:35.750 --> 37:36.917
- Yeah, no, I get it.

37:36.917 --> 37:38.417
- After another.
- I get it.

37:38.417 --> 37:40.292
When working on yachts,
there's times

37:40.292 --> 37:43.208
where you need to decide,
is it worth complaining about?

37:43.250 --> 37:44.875
Or would it take
just as much time

37:44.917 --> 37:47.292
just to do the job
rather than complain?

37:47.292 --> 37:49.958
- What's up?
- Will you tell your deck team

37:49.958 --> 37:51.958
that when we're in the middle
of breakfast service,

37:51.958 --> 37:54.750
that's too soon for us
to plan the cooler?

37:54.792 --> 37:57.250
Sierra, who asked you
to do the cooler?

37:57.292 --> 38:00.958
- Kyle.
- Thanks.

38:00.958 --> 38:02.708
- No problem.

38:05.083 --> 38:06.792
Kate's on a warpath.
- Why?

38:08.417 --> 38:10.125
- Yeah. Kate's on the warpath.

38:10.125 --> 38:15.125
What's new? I mean, first Ben,
then me, then Lauren.

38:15.125 --> 38:17.375
Who's she for next?
You, Kelley? Maybe Kyle.

38:17.417 --> 38:19.708
- We decorate their parties,
we stock their coolers

38:19.750 --> 38:21.833
for their guys.
We'll just do their job.

38:21.833 --> 38:24.083
We'll fill the cooler.
You know, it'd be nice

38:24.125 --> 38:25.917
if they cleared their stuff
so we could clean our--

38:25.958 --> 38:28.458
- It's the last day, man.

38:28.500 --> 38:30.292
Where's the love, man?

38:30.333 --> 38:33.792
Every time I have an interaction
with Sierra, there's drama.

38:33.833 --> 38:35.792
You might as well just buy
a ticket--it's box office.

38:35.833 --> 38:37.583
- Kate's just--
- Standard.

38:37.625 --> 38:40.792
- One more minute for that.
- We only have three meals left.

38:40.833 --> 38:44.000
So we should make this our
best lunch--our best dinner.

38:44.000 --> 38:47.667
Like, just 'cause they don't
have high-maintenance standards

38:47.667 --> 38:49.125
like Dean doesn't mean

38:49.167 --> 38:50.667
we shouldn't give them
Dean treatment.

38:50.667 --> 38:52.625
- Exactly.
- We were planning on doing

38:52.667 --> 38:53.833
a really bad service,

38:53.833 --> 38:56.333
so thanks for reminding us.

38:56.333 --> 38:57.792
- Will you go down to laundry?

38:57.833 --> 38:59.458
I think it's getting
a little bit crazy.

38:59.500 --> 39:02.333
- Yes, I will.
- Thank you.

39:02.375 --> 39:04.542
You know the beginning
of a football game

39:04.542 --> 39:06.042
where the coach gives a speech?

39:06.042 --> 39:07.625
I think the coach
would be annoyed

39:07.667 --> 39:09.375
if somebody was like,
"Oh, yeah, Coach, we were

39:09.375 --> 39:11.375
just gonna lose the game,
so why do you even talk to us?"

39:11.375 --> 39:12.958
- I didn't know
you were my coach.

39:13.000 --> 39:16.292
- I'm not; I was talking
to my stewardesses.

39:16.333 --> 39:18.625
I wasn't even talking to you.
I wasn't facing you.

39:18.667 --> 39:21.333
- I just won't talk.
I wish I was dead.

39:21.375 --> 39:23.125
- You're not on service.

39:23.167 --> 39:26.333
- Kate is just here
to spoil everyone's day again.

39:30.542 --> 39:32.125
- Oh, and so you thought
that would help?

39:32.167 --> 39:34.000
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

39:39.708 --> 39:39.917
- Coming up.

39:41.250 --> 39:43.208
- Oh, look
at that slide, perfect.

39:43.250 --> 39:46.750
- Cabling down, pull bow,
pull the bow.

39:46.792 --> 39:48.167
- Okay, you're off.

39:48.208 --> 39:49.750
- Are you going to enjoy
the baths with us?

39:49.792 --> 39:51.167
- Oh, no, I won't be going.

39:51.208 --> 39:53.000
The deck team
will actually take you.

39:53.042 --> 39:55.583
- When do you get a day off?
- Our season's almost over.

39:55.583 --> 39:56.833
- Oh.
- You're our last charter.

39:56.875 --> 39:59.208
- Oh?
- Yeah.

40:05.083 --> 40:06.417
- Snorkeling gear?
- Got it.

40:06.458 --> 40:08.167
- Cowls?
- Check.

40:08.208 --> 40:11.000
- Keys to the Tundress?
- There's also extra sunscreen

40:11.042 --> 40:12.417
in the top of the Esky.

40:12.458 --> 40:14.250
- Awesome.
- And that's it.

40:14.250 --> 40:15.750
- I was thinking of making
you guys a nice,

40:15.792 --> 40:17.917
refreshing cocktail
before you go to the baths.

40:17.958 --> 40:19.333
- Oh, I think that's
a great idea.

40:19.375 --> 40:20.750
- Yeah?

40:20.792 --> 40:22.250
Anytime any charter group

40:22.250 --> 40:24.750
wants to go to the baths
I am ecstatic...

40:24.750 --> 40:26.458
- You can sit wherever
you'd like.

40:26.458 --> 40:28.542
- Because I know they're
gonna have an amazing time.

40:28.583 --> 40:30.458
- Have a good trip.
- And I also know

40:30.500 --> 40:35.792
they're gonna be off the boat
for a solid three hours.

40:35.792 --> 40:38.125
Like, ugh.

40:38.167 --> 40:41.125
[tense music]

40:41.167 --> 40:48.625
♪ ♪

40:48.667 --> 40:51.042
Three out of four cabins
have no toilet paper.

40:51.083 --> 40:52.792
The master trashcan is full

40:52.792 --> 40:54.125
from things from
the night before.

40:54.167 --> 40:57.125
I thought Emily
and Sierra knew better

40:57.167 --> 41:02.125
and would respect me enough
to not just give up.

41:13.208 --> 41:17.167
- Okay, ladies.
- All right, boys.

41:17.167 --> 41:18.500
- All right, man.
- Y'all have fun.

41:18.500 --> 41:20.083
- Catch you later.

41:20.125 --> 41:22.833
All right, ladies, here we go.

41:22.875 --> 41:26.083
- So I know it's the last
full day of charter season,

41:26.125 --> 41:29.000
but this is the toilet
paper situation.

41:29.042 --> 41:31.750
- Where?
- This was in the twin room.

41:31.792 --> 41:33.500
This was in starboard forward.

41:33.500 --> 41:35.667
This was in port forward.

41:35.667 --> 41:41.000
So I want both of you girls
to go and conquer the cabins,

41:41.000 --> 41:43.250
vacuum, get all the spots
off the mirrors,

41:43.292 --> 41:44.833
make sure all
the toilet paper's filled--

41:44.833 --> 41:47.500
all the Kleenex paper
is filled so the boat

41:47.500 --> 41:48.917
looks really nice for when
the guests come back.

41:49.000 --> 41:50.667
- Yeah, sure.
- Thank you.

41:50.708 --> 41:53.708
This is resting
bitch face code red.

41:53.708 --> 41:55.375
Don't make me be the bad guy,

41:55.417 --> 41:58.208
because I can be a very bad,
bad guy.

41:58.208 --> 41:59.958
Then you don't
really need a break,

42:00.000 --> 42:01.792
and I go check all the cabins.

42:01.833 --> 42:03.958
The trashes are full, three of
the rooms have no toilet paper--

42:04.000 --> 42:06.042
like, none.
We don't need breaks.

42:06.083 --> 42:08.375
- It's the last day, of course
you don't need a break.

42:08.417 --> 42:10.208
- You're not tired
and the job's not done,

42:10.250 --> 42:11.958
clearly you haven't been
working enough.

42:14.583 --> 42:17.708
- Emily and I worked
so hard this season.

42:17.750 --> 42:19.375
And for her to say, like,

42:19.375 --> 42:22.375
that wasn't good enough,
it's bullsh--.

42:25.500 --> 42:27.708
- Next time on the season
finale of "Below Deck"...

42:27.750 --> 42:30.375
- Yay, tag team, boo-haha.

42:30.417 --> 42:33.583
- This time tomorrow.
- It's gonna be very naughty.

42:33.625 --> 42:36.083
- Yeah.
- I don't rat out my crew.

42:36.083 --> 42:37.417
I'm not done. I'm not done.
I'm not done.

42:37.417 --> 42:39.083
- Okay, well let's
just stop, Kate.

42:39.083 --> 42:40.917
Sierra's not a friend
to anybody; she's selfish.

42:40.917 --> 42:42.917
- Since I'm the chef I'm calling
the shots, Kate, so stop.

42:42.958 --> 42:45.333
I don't care anymore.
- All I asked--all I asked--

42:45.375 --> 42:47.083
- 'Cause I'm gonna do whatever
I want anyway,

42:47.083 --> 42:49.000
so there's actually no point
in fighting me.

42:49.042 --> 42:50.417
- You're such a jerk.
- I don't want to be dragged

42:50.417 --> 42:52.917
in on that situation,
and I won't.

42:52.917 --> 42:56.417
- Do you have a ring?
- Are you gonna propose?

42:56.458 --> 42:59.750
- Aww.
- Oh, my God!

42:59.750 --> 43:02.917
- I don't completely know
where they stand together,

43:02.958 --> 43:04.583
where we stand.

43:04.583 --> 43:07.917
- She brings out
a certain person in me

43:07.917 --> 43:09.750
that I don't want to be.

43:09.750 --> 43:12.958
I don't like working
with you anymore, that's it.

43:13.000 --> 43:15.417
- For more info,
go to Bravotv.com.
